    • Method Detail

      • update

        public void update()
        Description copied from interface: Updater
        This method should be used to force full update process of the associated editor content (tree of EditorCells)

        New UpdateSession instance will be created within this method and will be available via getCurrentUpdateSession() method until the end of update process, so it can be used from any code called as a sub-sequence of this method execution. E.g. the code generated from the editor aspect of any language.

        This method will set new rootCell for the associated EditorComponent.

        Internal update process-specific information about the model will be collected during this method execution and used later to update the editor incrementally.

        Specified by:
        update in interface Updater

      • getCurrentUpdateSession

        public UpdateSessionImpl getCurrentUpdateSession()
        Description copied from interface: Updater
        Return currently running update session or null if there is no active update session. UpdateSession will be created at the beginning of the rebuild process for the tree of EditorCells, as a sub-sequence of update process. UpdateSession will be stopped/disposed at the end of cell tree rebuild process.

        It's prohibited to execute another update before the end of currently running one. AssertionError will be thrown in such cases.

        Specified by:
        getCurrentUpdateSession in interface Updater
        Returns:
        currently running update session

      • setInitialEditorHints

        public boolean setInitialEditorHints​(@Nullable
                                     String[] hints)
        Description copied from interface: Updater
        Use this method to specify initial set of editor hints used by updater process to create EditorCell tree for the current editor. If null specified then default project-wide hints settings will be used.

        Return boolean value reflecting the fact that list of initialEditorHints were updated, so client should call explicit editor update (rebuild editor) in order to refresh current editor in accordance.

        Specified by:
        setInitialEditorHints in interface Updater
        Parameters:
        hints - array of hints or null if default settings should be used
        Returns:
        true if set of initialEditorHints were updated
